<td valign="top" colspan="2">
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; color: #000080;"><span style="font-size: 18pt;"><strong>Featured Item of the Month</strong></span></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; color: #000080;"><span style="font-size: 18pt;"> </span></span></p>
<p><img height="137" width="128" src="/images/stories/Books/Authors/Dr-Psomiadis.jpg" alt="Dr-Psomiadis" style="float: left; margin: 0px 10px 5px 0px;" /><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">This month, we are pleased to introduce <br />Dr. Harry Psomiadis' re-published book: </span></span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><br /></span></span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="color: #3366ff;"><strong>"The Eastern Question: the Last Phase: a Study in Greek-Turkish Diplomacy"</strong><br /></span><br />A sample chapter is included <span style="color: #ff6600;"><a last="last" target="_blank" href="/images/stories/Books/Articles/The_Exchange_of_Minorities-article.pdf" title="Expert from ">here</a></span> <br />for your review. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> <br /></span></span></span></span></span></span><em><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">*Please note: the views and conclusions <br />expressed in this article are those of the author <br />and do not necessarily represent the views of <br />the Pontian Greek Society of Chicago.</span></span></span></span></span></span></em></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> </span></span></span></span></span></span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">For more information on this book check our "Recommended Books <br />for Purchase" section below.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p></td>
</tr>



